==English==
===Verb===
'''to [[have]] [[had]] [[it]] [[up]] [[to]] [[here]]''' 
#{{idiom}} to have become very [[frustrated]] or [[angry]]; to have reached the [[limit]] of one's [[patience]] or [[forbearance]]
#:''I '''have had it up to here''' with this problem.''
#:''After fighting it all day, he '''has had it up to here'''.''

===Usage notes===
*takes ''with'' if an object is given
*when spoken, often accompanied by a hand [[gesture]] with a hand held high but parallel to the ground, as though indicating a high level
*rarely used in other tenses, e.g. '''have-''', '''has-''' or '''having it up to here'''

